            ">Citizenship consideration</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-10-1.jpg" alt="Citizenship consideration" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">President-elect Donald Trump <a href="https://www.politico.com/news/2024/12/08/trump-end-birthright-citizenship-00193184" target="_blank">reiterated</a> his intent to end birthright citizenship once he assumes office. However, he needed to clarify how he would circumvent the <a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/Fourteenth-Amendment" target="_blank">14th Amendment</a>, which guarantees citizenship to those born on U.S. soil. Despite claiming executive action as a potential avenue, there are many legal hurdles, including the constitutional amendment process requiring state ratification.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The US is one of the countries that provides citizenship by <a href="https://www.britannica.com/topic/jus-soli" target="_blank">Jus soli</a>, meaning 'right of soil,' which gives anyone born in the territory of the state automatic nationality or citizenship with a few exceptions. This is a typical pattern between most countries in the Western Hemisphere. While Trump did speak on making harsher immigration stances, he did express openness to working with Democrats on a solution for <a href="https://www.newsweek.com/donald-trump-reveals-key-issue-where-he-wants-work-democrats-1997309" target="_blank">Dreamers</a>, highlighting their long-standing ties to the U.S. Many <a href="https://www.uscis.gov/DACA" target="_blank">DACA</a> recipients have been in the country for years and likely have no connection to their country of birth.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
